e:T459,Soybeans are the world's dominant oilseed, feeding the global crush complex for soybean meal (animal feed protein) and soybean oil. XRT Group sources USDA Grade No. 1 soybeans from US Gulf and Brazilian Paranaguá export terminals for crushers, feed integrators, and food-grade processors.

**Quality Specification**

USDA Grade No. 1: maximum 13% moisture, 1% foreign material, 2% splits, 0.2% heat-damaged kernels. Updated FGIS 2025 sampling protocol applied (six spear probes per 1,000 MT). Intertek conducts load-port composite analysis.

**Logistics**

Panamax bulk loading at USGC and Paranaguá. Typical transit: 22–26 days USGC to China, 30–35 days to Southeast Asia.

**Pricing**

CBOT soybeans futures-basis pricing. XRT's current indicative CFR premium: +$7.00/MT. Crush-margin-linked term structures available through our Agricultural desk.

**Contract Terms**

GAFTA 100 standard. LC issuance per UCP 600. Destination sampling rights addressed in the quality determination clause.

**Typical Buyers**

Oilseed crushers, soybean meal feed producers, food-grade soy processors, government reserves.7:["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-12 pt-10 sm:pt-16 pb-10 sm:pb-12","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_400px] gap-10 lg:gap-16 items-start","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-6","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"label-caps px-3 py-1.5 border","style":{"color":"#c8973a","borderColor":"#c8973a"},"children":"AGR-003"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"label-caps text-xrt-steel/40","children":"Grains & Agricultural"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-[clamp(2.25rem,6vw,4.5rem)] text-white leading-[1.0] mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-barlow)","fontWeight":900,"letterSpacing":"-0.02em","textTransform":"uppercase"},"children":"Soybeans No. 1"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base text-xrt-steel/50 mb-8","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-archivo)","letterSpacing":"0.04em"},"children":"13% Moisture / 1% FM"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base sm:text-lg text-xrt-steel/70 leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-xl","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-archivo)"},"children":"USDA No. 1 Soybeans from US Gulf and Paranaguá terminals. 13% moisture, 1% foreign material. CBOT Soybeans benchmark at +$7.00/MT. Minimum 30,000 MT, CFR. Intertek inspection. GAFTA 100 terms."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 border-t border-xrt-steel/15","children":[["$","div","Min. Volume",{"className":"py-5 sm:py-6 border-b sm:border-b-0 sm:border-r border-xrt-steel/15 sm:px-6 sm:first:pl-0","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"label-caps text-xrt-steel/40 mb-2","children":"Min. Volume"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-black text-white","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-barlow)","letterSpacing":"-0.02em"},"children":"30,000 MT"}]]}],["$","div","Benchmark",{"className":"py-5 sm:py-6 border-b sm:border